### ğŸğŸªœ Snake and Ladder Game in Java (Console)

```java
import java.util.*;

public class SnakeAndLadder {

    static Map<Integer, Integer> snakes = new HashMap<>();
    static Map<Integer, Integer> ladders = new HashMap<>();
    static Random random = new Random();

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Define snakes
        snakes.put(99, 21);
        snakes.put(95, 75);
        snakes.put(92, 88);
        snakes.put(89, 68);
        snakes.put(74, 53);
        snakes.put(62, 19);
        snakes.put(49, 11);
        snakes.put(46, 25);
        snakes.put(16, 6);

        // Define ladders
        ladders.put(2, 38);
        ladders.put(7, 14);
        ladders.put(8, 31);
        ladders.put(15, 26);
        ladders.put(21, 42);
        ladders.put(28, 84);
        ladders.put(36, 44);
        ladders.put(51, 67);
        ladders.put(71, 91);
        ladders.put(78, 98);
        ladders.put(87, 94);

        int[] positions = {0, 0};
        int currentPlayer = 0;

        System.out.println("ğŸ® Welcome to Snake and Ladder Game!");
        System.out.println("Player 1 and Player 2 start at position 0.");

        while (true) {
            System.out.println("\nPlayer " + (currentPlayer + 1) + "'s turn. Press enter to roll the dice...");
            sc.nextLine();
            int dice = rollDice();
            System.out.println("You rolled a " + dice + "!");

            int newPos = positions[currentPlayer] + dice;
            if (newPos > 100) {
                System.out.println("Roll exceeds 100. Stay at " + positions[currentPlayer]);
            } else {
                positions[currentPlayer] = newPos;
                System.out.println("Moved to " + newPos);
                if (snakes.containsKey(newPos)) {
                    positions[currentPlayer] = snakes.get(newPos);
                    System.out.println("Oh no! Bitten by a snake ğŸ. Slid down to " + positions[currentPlayer]);
                } else if (ladders.containsKey(newPos)) {
                    positions[currentPlayer] = ladders.get(newPos);
                    System.out.println("Yay! Climbed a ladder ğŸªœ. Moved up to " + positions[currentPlayer]);
                }
            }

            if (positions[currentPlayer] == 100) {
                System.out.println("ğŸ‰ Player " + (currentPlayer + 1) + " wins the game!");
                break;
            }

            currentPlayer = 1 - currentPlayer;
        }

        sc.close();
    }

    static int rollDice() {
        return random.nextInt(6) + 1;
    }
}
```

---

### âœ… Features:

* Classic 1 to 100 board
* Predefined snakes and ladders
* Two-player mode
* Text-based console interface

---

### ğŸ§ª How to Run:

1. Save the code as `SnakeAndLadder.java`
2. Compile: `javac SnakeAndLadder.java`
3. Run: `java SnakeAndLadder`

